page.title: 13Housing in Filey.
page.content: In the 17 century fishing cottages were built they were made of stone and painted white.They still stand today near the museum on Queen Street Filey. In the late 1960's a new estate was built it was called Wharfedale.Before the estate was built it was fields and woodlands. In the 1960's new homes were built by a company called Ideal Homes.They built a big estate near the church,St. Oswalds,which was built in the 12th century. Recently this year builders moved into an old derelict playschool they knocked it down and built flats for old people.
